{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> ἄλῡπ-ος</b>, ον, <br /> <b>without pain,</b> frequently in Trag. (not [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus), 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Iphigenia Aulidensis” 163, etc.: with _genitive_, ἄ. γήρως\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>] <b>without pains</b> of age, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Oedipus Coloneus” 1519; ἄ. ἄτης “El.” 1002; βίος 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Bacchae” 1004; ἀρχή 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Oedipus Tyrannus” 593; τὸ ἄ. 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Respublica” 585a: _comparative_ -ότερος [prev. work] 581e\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: <i>superlative</i> <b>-ότατος</b>[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “Lg.” 848e. \">Refs</a>]<i>adverb</i> ἀλύπως, ζῆν, διατελεῖν live <b>free from pain and sorrow,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “Prt.” 358b, “Phlb.” 43d, compare 4th-3rd c.BC: Menander Comicus 549; ἀποθανεῖν [prev. author] 14\">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]: <i>superlative</i> ἀλυπότατα[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Lysias Orator 24.10. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> <i>active</i>, <b>causing no pain</b> or <b>grief,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Hippocrates Medicus “περὶ ἄρθρων ἐμβολῆς” 39 (_superlative_), 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Politicus” 272a, etc.; ἄ. οἶνος \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<b>harmless,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Hermippus Comicus 82.5, compare 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Bacchae” 423\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ἄ. ἄνθος ἀνίας <b>setting free from the pain</b> of sorrow of wine, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Fragmenta” 172\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ἀλυπότατος κλιντήρ, of a hospice, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “epigram Gr.” 450 (from Batanaea)\">Refs</a>]; σωλῆνες -ότατοι μετὰ ἁλῶν <b>cause least pain,</b> i.e. <b>are least indigestible,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st c.AD: Xenocrates Medicus 57, cf. Mnesith. cited in 2nd c.AD: Athenaeus Epigrammaticus 3.92c; πεσσὸς -ότατος 6th c.AD: Aëtius Medicus 16.36. \">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]<i>adverb</i> ἀλύπως, τοῖς ἄλλοις ζῆν live <b>without offence</b> to others, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Isocrates Orator 12.5. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__III</b></Level2> ἄλυπον, τό, <b>herb terrible, Globularia Alypum,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st c.AD: Plinius Rerum Naturalium Scriptor “Historia Naturalis” 27.22, 1st c.AD: Dioscorides (Dioscurides) Medicus 4.178.\">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]","strongNumber":"G0253","accentedUnicode":"ἄλυπος","relatedNos":[{"strongNumber":"G3077","matchingForm":"λύπη","stepTransliteration":"lupē","gloss":"grief","_zh_tw_Gloss":"憂愁","_es_Gloss":"aflicción","_zh_Gloss":"忧愁"}],"shortDef":"free from anxiety; in the comparative, less anxiety","mediumDef":"free from anxiety; in the comparative, less anxiety <br /><b>free from grief</b>, or <b>sorrow,</b> <ref='Php.2.28'>Phil. 2:28</ref>*","stepGloss":"without anxiety","stepTransliteration":"alupos","count":1,"_es_Definition":"sin ansiedad o tristeza","_zh_tw_Definition":"沒有悲傷的(腓 2:28)","_zh_Definition":"没有悲伤的(腓 2:28)","_step_Type":"word","_vi_Definition":"tự do từ đau hoặc đau buồn; chẳng buồn rầu hơn","_zh_tw_Gloss":"沒有憂愁","_es_Gloss":"sin ansiedad","_zh_Gloss":"没有忧愁"}]}